goals.question: What is the trend of the number of incidents reported during the LA riots?
goals.visualization: Line chart of the number of incidents reported over time
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us understand the intensity of the riots and how it evolved over time.

goals.question: What is the distribution of the type of incidents reported during the LA riots?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of the count of each type of incident
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us identify the most common types of incidents and their relative frequency.

goals.question: What is the geographic distribution of the incidents reported during the LA riots?
goals.visualization: Heatmap of the incidents reported by location
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us identify the hotspots of the riots and how they spread across the city.

goals.question: What is the relationship between the number of incidents reported and the time of day?
goals.visualization: Line chart of the number of incidents reported by hour of the day
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us identify the peak hours of the riots and how they correlate with other factors such as curfew or police presence.

goals.question: What is the demographic distribution of the victims and perpetrators of the incidents reported during the LA riots?
goals.visualization: Stacked bar chart of the count of incidents by race and role (victim or perpetrator)
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us understand the social dynamics of the riots and how they affected different communities.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.dates as mdates

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['date'] = data['date'].dt.to_period('D')
    daily_incidents = data.groupby('date').size().reset_index(name='incidents')

    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='incidents', data=daily_incidents, ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of the number of incidents reported during the LA riots?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Incidents')
    ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%Y-%m-%d'))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    incident_counts = data['incident_type'].value_counts()
    sns.barplot(x=incident_counts.index, y=incident_counts.values, palette='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('Incident Type')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the type of incidents reported during the LA riots?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(incident_counts.index, title='Incident Types', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['latitude', 'longitude'])
    heatmap_data = data[['latitude', 'longitude']]
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
    sns.set(style="white")
    sns.kdeplot(heatmap_data['longitude'], heatmap_data['latitude'], cmap="coolwarm", shade=True, shade_lowest=False)
    plt.title("What is the geographic distribution of the incidents reported during the LA riots?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Longitude")
    plt.ylabel("Latitude")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]
    data['hour'] = data['time'].dt.hour
    hourly_incidents = data.groupby('hour').size().reset_index(name='incidents')

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='hour', y='incidents', data=hourly_incidents)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between the number of incidents reported and the time of day?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Hour of the Day')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Incidents Reported')
    plt.xticks(range(0, 24))
    plt.legend(['Incidents per Hour'])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

chart = plot(data)
